We are given a input string, we have to reverse it with out duplicating it.

We use two pointers(left and right) and a temporary variable.

Algorithm:
Step 1: Initialize left =0 and right = input_array_length-1
Step 2: while left < right , we  store array[left] in a temp variable and swap array[left] with array[right] and array[left] with temp

class Solution {
    public void reverseString(char[] s) {

        int left =0, right = s.length-1;

        while(left<right)
        {
            char temp = s[left];

            s[left] = s[right];
            s[right] = temp;
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        
    }
}
